==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bona fide
<hw>Bo"na fi"de</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>In or with
good faith; without fraud or deceit; real or really; actual or actually;
genuine or genuinely; <as>as, you must proceed <ex>bona fide</ex>; a
<ex>bona fide</ex> purchaser or transaction</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bona fides</ent>⟦br⟧
